THIRD-PARTY API TERMS AND CONDITIONS

This software integrates with third-party carrier APIs. Users of this software
MUST comply with the terms of service of each carrier API they use:

1. DHL Express Tracking API
   - Terms: https://developer.dhl.com/legal
   - Users must obtain their own API keys from DHL
   - Users are responsible for compliance with DHL API terms
   - DHL trademarks and data remain property of DHL

2. FedEx Track API
   - Terms: https://developer.fedex.com/terms
   - Users must obtain their own API credentials from FedEx
   - Users are responsible for compliance with FedEx API terms
   - FedEx trademarks and data remain property of FedEx Corporation

3. UPS Tracking API
   - Terms: https://www.ups.com/upsdeveloperkit/downloadresource/agreementhtml
   - Users must obtain their own API credentials from UPS
   - Users are responsible for compliance with UPS API terms
   - UPS trademarks and data remain property of United Parcel Service

BY USING THIS SOFTWARE WITH ANY CARRIER API, YOU AGREE TO:
- Obtain proper authorization and API keys from each carrier
- Comply with rate limits and usage restrictions
- Honor carrier terms of service and data usage policies
- Not use the software for unauthorized commercial purposes without carrier approval
- Indemnify the software authors from any API terms violations

DISCLAIMER:
The authors of this software are not affiliated with DHL, FedEx, UPS, or any
carrier. This software is provided as a tool to help users access carrier APIs
they are authorized to use. The authors assume no responsibility for misuse of
carrier APIs or violations of carrier terms of service.

